Subject: [PATCH] fix(planning): close canvas persistence and conversion gaps

This patch is the full corrective implementation for Planning Canvas after PR #324 was merged with only the helper/test files.

Apply with:

git apply docs/planning-gap-closure-corrective.patch

Then run:

npm ci
npm run typecheck
npm test -- --run src/features/planning/state/slices/planningElementIds.test.ts src/features/planning/state/slices/selectionSlice.test.ts
npm run build

Summary of intended changes:

- Use persistable UUID ids for new Planning Canvas elements instead of nanoid-based ids.
- Cover addElement, addText, pen strokes, paste/duplicate, smart elements, text helpers, and frame creation.
- Prevent smart conversion for legacy/non-persistable selected ids.
- Make smart conversion required records fail loudly instead of best-effort allSettled writes.
- Make Smart Docs persistence typed and non-silent.
- Align frontend AI permission with canvas.ai.use.
- Harden board/global role merge logic.
- Add focused tests for persistable ids.

Full patch is available in the local Codex workspace as commit 410dc32d if this patch file is truncated by transport.
